          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p>mostly yiddish German</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Baltimore</placeName>-On <date>1<hi
                                                  rend="sup">st</hi> day of Rosh Hodesh</date></p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">
                                        <date>of second Adar____1848?</date>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">To my beloved, my loyal friend, full of good<lb/>
                                        qualites etc. <persName>Eliezer</persName>-may he live
                                        forever<lb/> I have come with this letter to fulfill<lb/>
                                        your request, and to write out in order<lb/> the prayer,
                                        "God full of mercy"<lb/> ([)Here follows the Hishkaba(])</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Evidently, my dear, you have for-<lb/>gotten that
                                        I wrote to you at the end<lb/> of last year that my
                                        circumstances<lb/> do not permit me to continue to receive the<lb/>
                                        <hi rend="underline">Kol Ya-a-kob</hi>. I shall therefore
                                        take<lb/> up the copies you have sent me so far<lb/> until I
                                        can safely return them to you.<lb/> I <del>shall</del> want
                                        to receive the "<hi rend="underline">Zir
                                        Ne-e-<lb/>man</hi>". but will not pay the money in<lb/>
                                        advance since usually such works<lb/> are begun but never completed.<lb/>
                                        <del>Thus, for example,</del> I think you</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>will agree with me in this matter. I paid<lb/> for the Kos
                                        Ye-shu-oth, and to this day no<lb/> more than ten
                                        installments have appeared though<lb/> there should have
                                        been twelve of them.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I really pained by the fact that<lb/>
                                        <persName>Mister Pope</persName> has not sent you his
                                        speeches<lb/> For, my dearly beloved, to you I reveal
                                        my<lb/> heart and soul. I tremble because I have<lb/> to
                                        preach every <date>Sabbath</date>, and a man like<lb/> me,
                                        who has troubles private and public,<lb/> must very often
                                        rely upon outside aid<lb/> in order to be able to preach in
                                        public<lb/> frequently. If you will occasionally help<lb/>
                                        me with understanding, it will be accounted<lb/> as a great
                                        Mitzvah to you. I hope that<lb/> in this way I shall not
                                        interrupt my<lb/> constant preoccupation in the study
                                        of<lb/> our sacred Torah.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I remain as ever your true friend<lb/> and
                                        well-wisher.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(7)">
                                        <persName role="author">Abraham Reis</persName>
                              </p>
                    </body>
